好了。

174
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,180
We're back.
我们回来了。

175
00:07:46,180 --> 00:07:52,380
Why don't we take a look at Fluency Builder and start taking a look at all these phrases.
我们来看看“流利度构建器”，开始学习所有这些短语。

176
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:53,380
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

177
00:07:53,380 --> 00:08:00,060
Well, the first one is something that we often say when we're starting to feel ill.
第一个是我们开始感觉不舒服时常说的话。

178
00:08:00,060 --> 00:08:02,220
This phrase is coming down with.
这个短语是“coming down with”。

179
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:06,220
So I could say, I think I'm coming down with a cold, for example.
所以我可以这样说，比如，我觉得我快感冒了。

180
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:09,660
So basically, you say, I'm coming down with something.
基本上，你会说，我好像要生病了。

181
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:13,180
So a cold or I think I'm coming down with the flu.
比如感冒，或者我觉得我快得流感了。

182
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:15,780
So you're saying that I think I'm getting ill?
所以你的意思是，我觉得我快生病了？

183
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:16,780
Exactly.
没错。

184
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:19,420
It means I'm just starting to feel sick.
意思是我刚开始感觉不舒服。

185
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:22,420
And so you could say, I've had a cold for a week.
所以你可以说，我感冒已经一周了。

186
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:25,220
You wouldn't use the phrase I'm coming down with in this situation.
在这种情况下你不会用“coming down with”这个短语。

187
00:08:25,220 --> 00:08:28,260
You'd only use it when you're starting to feel sick.
你只在刚开始感觉不舒服时用它。

188
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:29,260
Very good.
很好。

189
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:31,980
So you could ask your boss, I think I'm coming down with the flu.
所以你可以对老板说，我觉得我快得流感了。

190
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,860
Can I go home early?
我能早点回家吗？

191
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:35,040
Right.
对。

192
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:37,220
And I think this is a very useful phrase.
我觉得这是个很有用的短语。

193
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:39,860
It's very natural to say.
说起来很自然。

194
00:08:39,860 --> 00:08:43,740
So why don't we listen to a couple of other examples?
那我们再听几个其他例子吧。

195
00:08:43,740 --> 00:08:45,980
Example one.
例子一。

196
00:08:45,980 --> 00:08:47,780
Honey will you take my temperature?
亲爱的，你能帮我量体温吗？

197
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:51,500
I think I'm coming down with something.
我觉得我好像要生病了。

198
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,580
Example two.
例子二。

199
00:08:53,580 --> 00:08:57,700
You must be coming down with a cold.
你一定是快感冒了。

200
00:08:57,700 --> 00:09:01,380
Example three.
例子三。

201
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:05,100
Tommy came down with the flu.
Tommy得了流感。

202
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,100
All right.
好的。

203
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:10,460
So coming down with, coming down with the flu, coming down with a cough, etc.
所以“coming down with”，得了流感，得了咳嗽等等。

204
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:11,460
All right.
好的。

205
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:12,460
What's our next phrase?
我们下一个短语是什么？

206
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:13,460
Well, this one's great.
嗯，这个很棒。

207
00:09:13,460 --> 00:09:14,980
It's a filler phrase.
这是一个填充短语。

208
00:09:14,980 --> 00:09:17,660
So in the meantime.
所以是“in the meantime”。

209
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:19,420
In the meantime.
“In the meantime”。

210
00:09:19,420 --> 00:09:23,580
So I could say, all right, I'm going to go cook dinner.
所以我可以这么说：好的，我要去做晚饭了。

211
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:26,620
In the meantime, Marco, can you please clear the table?
与此同时，Marco，你能把桌子收拾一下吗？

212
00:09:26,620 --> 00:09:27,620
Okay.
好的。

213
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:31,980
So while you are cooking dinner, I am doing something else.
所以当你做晚饭的时候，我在做别的事情。

214
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:32,980
I'm cleaning the table.
我在擦桌子。

215
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:34,540
So two things happening at the same time.
所以两件事同时发生。

216
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:35,540
In the meantime.
“In the meantime”。

217
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:36,540
Very good.
非常好。

218
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:38,020
So it's a filler, you say.
所以你说它是一个填充词。

219
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:39,860
Because usually it follows another phrase.
因为它通常跟在另一个短语后面。

220
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:42,180
So I'm going to be doing this report for a while.
所以我要花一段时间做这份报告。

221
00:09:42,180 --> 00:09:46,300
In the meantime, can you just wait here on the sofa, please?
与此同时，你能在沙发上等一下吗？

222
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:47,300
Okay.
好的。

223
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,300
Very good.
非常好。

224
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,300
So in the meantime.
所以是“in the meantime”。

225
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,380
So you're connecting two different actions, two different ideas.
所以你在连接两个不同的动作、两个不同的想法。

226
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,380
Exactly.
没错。

227
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:53,380
Very good.
非常好。

228
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:54,380
In the meantime.
“In the meantime”。

229
00:09:54,380 --> 00:09:56,020
And what about our last phrase?
那我们最后一个短语呢？

230
00:09:56,020 --> 00:09:57,500
All right.
好的。

231
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:00,060
There are some people who really like to do this.
有些人真的很喜欢这样做。

232
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:01,780
And I might be one of them.
我可能就是其中之一。

233
00:10:01,780 --> 00:10:05,180
It's called to blow things out of proportion.
这叫做“把小事夸大”。

234
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:06,180
All right.
好的。

235
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:09,820
And you're going to hear this phrase a lot with native English speakers.
你会经常听到母语为英语的人说这个短语。

236
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:16,420
And so to blow things out of proportion, well, it pretty much means that you're exaggerating
所以“to blow things out of proportion”，基本上意思是你夸大其词，

237
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:22,340
or you're making a really big deal out of something that's not very serious.
或者你把一件不太严重的事情搞得很大。

238
00:10:22,340 --> 00:10:26,300
So for example, if you come over to my house and you break a glass and I start freaking
比如，如果你来我家，打碎了一个杯子，然后我抓狂，

239
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:28,460
out and yelling at you because you broke my glass.
冲你大喊大叫，因为你打碎了我的杯子。

240
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:31,180
I say, Marco, you're blowing things out of proportion.
我会说：Marco，你把事情夸大了。

241
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:32,340
I'll just buy you a new one.
我给你买个新的就行了。

242
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,340
It's not that serious.
没那么严重。

243
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:34,340
All right.
好吧。

244
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,340
So don't exaggerate.
所以别夸张了。

245
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,340
Right.
对。

246
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:37,340
Right.
对。

247
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:44,340
And you can say like this with siblings, spouses or bosses who react very seriously.
你可以这样对兄弟姐妹、配偶或反应很严肃的老板说。

248
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:46,540
So you can say, hey, stop.
所以你可以说，嘿，停下。

249
00:10:46,540 --> 00:10:49,100
Stop yelling like you're blowing things out of proportion.
别大喊大叫，好像你在小题大做。

250
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:51,620
This is not a really big deal.
这真的不是什么大事。

251
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:52,620
Exactly.
没错。

252
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:53,620
All right.
好吧。

253
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:55,340
So blowing things out of proportion.
所以“小题大做”就是这个意思。

254
00:10:55,340 --> 00:10:56,340
Let's not do that.
我们别那样做。

255
00:10:56,340 --> 00:11:08,060
Let's listen to our dialogue for the last time and then we'll be back.
让我们最后听一遍对话，然后回来。

256
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,060
What's wrong with you?
你怎么了？

257
00:11:09,060 --> 00:11:10,060
Why are you scratching so much?
你怎么挠得这么厉害？

258
00:11:10,060 --> 00:11:11,060
I feel itchy.
我觉得痒。

259
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:12,060
I can't stand it anymore.
我受不了了。

260
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:13,060
I think I may be coming down with something.
我想我可能生病了。

261
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,060
I feel lightheaded and weak.
我觉得头晕无力。

262
00:11:14,060 --> 00:11:15,060
Let me have a look.
让我看看。

263
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,060
Whoa, get away from me.
哇，离我远点。

264
00:11:16,060 --> 00:11:17,060
What's wrong?
怎么了？

265
00:11:17,060 --> 00:11:18,060
I think you have chicken pox.
我觉得你得了水痘。

266
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:28,340
You're contagious.
你会传染的。

267
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:29,340
Get away.
走开。

268
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:30,340
Don't breathe on me.
别对着我呼吸。

269
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:32,420
Maybe it's just a rash or an allergy.
可能只是皮疹或过敏。

270
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:34,540
We can't be sure until I see a doctor.
在看过医生之前我们不能确定。

271
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:37,460
Well, in the meantime, you're a biohazard.
嗯，在那之前，你就是个生物危害。

272
00:11:37,460 --> 00:11:41,260
I didn't get it when I was a kid and I've heard that you can even die if you get it
我小时候没得过，而且我听说如果成年后得水痘，

273
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:42,260
as an adult.
甚至可能会死。

274
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:43,260
Are you serious?
你是认真的吗？

275
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:45,700
You always blow things out of proportion.
你总是小题大做。

276
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:50,740
In any case, I think I'll go take an oatmeal bath.
不管怎样，我想我去洗个燕麦浴。

277
00:11:50,740 --> 00:11:52,740
Eww.
呃。

278
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:56,460
All right.
好吧。

279
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,940
So Catherine, have you ever had the chicken pox?
那么凯瑟琳，你得过水痘吗？

280
00:11:58,940 --> 00:11:59,940
I did.
我得过。

281
00:11:59,940 --> 00:12:04,780
I have very, very clear memories of when I was a child and I had the chicken pox because
我对自己小时候出水痘的记忆非常非常清晰，因为

282
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:10,620
I believe it was Thanksgiving and I was about four or five years old.
我记得那是在感恩节，我当时大概四五岁。

283
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:14,660
And I didn't have an appetite, so I was not hungry.
我没有胃口，所以不觉得饿。

284
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:16,540
And all I could do was itch and drink.
我唯一能做的就是挠痒和喝水。

285
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:20,860
And so I still have little scars like you mentioned from where I couldn't stop myself
所以就像你提到的，我身上还留着一些小疤痕，因为我忍不住

286
00:12:20,860 --> 00:12:23,100
from scratching my little marks.
去抓那些小印记。

287
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,100
Right.
对。

288
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:28,620
And well, why does the little boy say that he's going to go take an oatmeal bath?
那么，那个小男孩为什么说他要去洗燕麦浴呢？

289
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:29,620
An oatmeal bath.
燕麦浴。

290
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:30,620
Okay.
好的。

291
00:12:30,620 --> 00:12:36,300
Well, this is one of the home remedies, one of the home cures for the itchiness.
嗯，这是一种家庭疗法，一种缓解瘙痒的家庭偏方。

292
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:37,340
All right.
明白了。

293
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:42,940
So it doesn't make your chicken pox go away, but it does make your skin feel better because
所以它不会让水痘消失，但能让你的皮肤感觉好一些，因为

294
00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:44,620
it's very calming and smooth.
它非常舒缓和平滑。

295
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:49,780
So you can have some creams or some lotions, but other people like to take an oatmeal bath.
所以你可以用一些药膏或乳液，但其他人喜欢洗燕麦浴。

296
00:12:49,780 --> 00:12:50,780
Right.
对。

297
00:12:50,780 --> 00:12:52,140
So then you're not itching anymore.
这样你就不再痒了。

298
00:12:52,140 --> 00:12:53,140
Right.
对。

299
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:55,980
But it's gross because you're sitting in oatmeal.
但坐在燕麦里感觉挺恶心的。

300
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:56,980
It is kind of gross.
是有点恶心。

301
00:12:56,980 --> 00:12:59,300
Have you had the chicken pox?
你得过水痘吗？

302
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:02,100
I didn't know because I couldn't remember.
我不知道，因为我记不清了。

303
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:06,420
So actually my brother had it recently, so I was afraid that I didn't get it, but I called
实际上我哥哥最近得了水痘，所以我担心自己没得过，但我打电话

304
00:13:06,420 --> 00:13:07,420
my mom.
问了我妈妈。

305
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:08,820
She said I got it, so I'm good.
她说我得过，所以我没事。

306
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:09,820
You're safe.
你安全了。

307
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:10,820
Yeah.
是的。

308
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:11,820
So that's the thing, right?
所以就是这样，对吧？

309
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:12,820
You can only get it once.
你只会得一次。

310
00:13:12,820 --> 00:13:14,620
You don't have a problem.
你没有问题。

311
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:17,260
Well, we're curious to know, have you had the chicken pox?
嗯，我们很好奇，你得过水痘吗？

312
00:13:17,260 --> 00:13:22,100
And if you did, was it really itchy or were you a lucky one and it wasn't so bad?
如果得过，是不是特别痒，还是你幸运，没那么严重？

313
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:24,140
So let us know on our website, englishpod.com.
所以请在我们的网站 englishpod.com 上告诉我们。

314
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:25,140
Right.
对。

315
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:30,740
And if you ever had any other common childhood illnesses like the mumps or the measles, right,
如果你还得过其他常见的儿童疾病，比如腮腺炎或麻疹，对吧，

316
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,640
you can also tell us about that.
你也可以告诉我们。

317
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,820
So we'll see you guys there and until next time.
那我们就在那里见，下次再见。

318
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:35,820
Bye everyone.
大家再见。

319
00:13:35,820 --> 00:13:49,760
Enter a culture in which a child lives above the parents by invoking a parenting image
进入一种文化，在这种文化中，孩子通过唤起自己童年的父母形象来凌驾于父母之上。

320
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,720
of their childhood.
他们童年的形象。

321
00:13:51,720 --> 00:14:04,680
So the clan really started out by messing around with the cards they thought about
所以这个家族一开始就是通过摆弄那些他们想到的卡片起步的。
